---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Growth Services for HVAC, Roofing & Plumbing | Built on Tenth" description="Revenue Leak Audits, Growth Blueprints, and 90-Day Advisory for home service companies.">

<style>
.services-intro{padding:4rem 2.5rem;background:var(--cream);text-align:center}
.services-intro p{font-size:1.05rem;color:var(--text-mid);max-width:600px;margin:0 auto;line-height:1.7}
.sd{padding:5rem 2.5rem}.sd:nth-child(odd){background:var(--warm-white)}
.sd-inner{max-width:960px;margin:0 auto;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:4rem;align-items:center}
.sd-inner.reverse{direction:rtl}.sd-inner.reverse>*{direction:ltr}
.sd-text h2{font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:clamp(1.6rem,3vw,2.2rem);font-weight:800;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:0.5rem;line-height:1.15}
.sd-price{font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:var(--amber-dark);margin-bottom:1rem}
.sd-text p{font-size:0.95rem;color:var(--text-mid);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:1rem}
.sd-features{list-style:none;margin:1.5rem 0}
.sd-features li{display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:0.6rem;padding:0.45rem 0;font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--text-dark);line-height:1.5}
.sd-features li::before{content:'\2713';color:var(--green-accent);font-weight:700;flex-shrink:0}
.sd-visual{background:var(--navy);border-radius:16px;padding:2.5rem;color:#fff}
.sd-visual h3{font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:1.5rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.6)}
.sd-row{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;padding:0.7rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);font-size:0.85rem}
.sd-row:last-child{border-bottom:none}
.sd-row span:first-child{color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5)}.sd-row .bad{color:var(--red-accent);font-weight:600}.sd-row .good{color:var(--green-accent);font-weight:600}.sd-row .amber{color:var(--amber);font-weight:600}

.faq-section{padding:5rem 2.5rem;background:var(--cream)}.faq-inner{max-width:700px;margin:0 auto}
.faq-inner h2{font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.8rem;font-weight:800;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:2rem;text-align:center}
.faq-item{border-bottom:1px solid var(--warm-gray)}
.faq-q{padding:1.25rem 0;cursor:pointer;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:700;font-size:0.95rem;color:var(--navy)}
.faq-q::after{content:'+';font-size:1.2rem;color:var(--amber-dark);transition:transform 0.3s}.faq-q.open::after{transform:rotate(45deg)}
.faq-a{max-height:0;overflow:hidden;transition:max-height 0.4s ease}
.faq-a-inner{padding:0 0 1.25rem;font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--text-mid);line-height:1.65}
@media(max-width:768px){.sd-inner,.sd-inner.reverse{grid-template-columns:1fr;direction:ltr}}
</style>

<section class="page-hero">
  <h1>Stop guessing. <em>Start knowing.</em></h1>
  <p>Every engagement starts with data and ends with a system. No contracts. No recurring fees. No calls required.</p>
</section>

<section class="services-intro reveal"><p>Start with the audit. Upgrade to the blueprint if you want the full system. Add advisory if you want us guiding implementation. Every step builds on the last.</p></section>

<section class="sd" id="audit"><div class="sd-inner reveal">
  <div class="sd-text">
    <div class="section-label">Service 01</div>
    <h2>Revenue Leak Audit</h2>
    <div class="sd-price">$750</div>
    <p>Most HVAC owners are spending $5K–$15K/month on marketing with no clear picture of what's actually producing jobs. This audit shows you exactly where your money is going — and what each gap is costing you annually.</p>
    <p style="font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;">What you walk away with: a complete picture of your marketing performance in dollars, benchmarked against your top competitors, with a prioritized list of exactly what to fix first.</p>
    <ul class="sd-features">
      <li>Google Business Profile vs. top 5–7 local competitors — gap translated to estimated calls lost</li>
      <li>Website conversion audit — every leak that's costing you contacts and calls</li>
      <li>Google Ads and LSA assessment — are you getting jobs or funding click fraud</li>
      <li>Review ecosystem analysis — reputation gap and what it costs in map pack position</li>
      <li>Every single finding expressed as annual revenue impact in dollars</li>
      <li>Prioritized action list — what to fix this week, this month, this quarter</li>
      <li>15–25 page report delivered in 7 business days</li>
    </ul>
    <a href="mailto:hello@builtontenth.com?subject=Revenue Leak Audit" class="btn-primary">Apply for an Audit &rarr;</a>
  </div>
  <div class="sd-visual">
    <h3>Sample audit findings</h3>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Google reviews vs. top competitor</span><span class="bad">47 vs. 230</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Estimated calls lost to gap</span><span class="bad">15-25/mo</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Google Ads conversion tracking</span><span class="bad">Not installed</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Monthly spend without tracking</span><span class="bad">$4,200 blind</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Website mobile load time</span><span class="bad">6.2 seconds</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Estimate follow-up system</span><span class="bad">None</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Phone answer rate</span><span class="good">Strong</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span style="color:#fff;font-weight:600">Total estimated annual leakage</span><span class="bad" style="font-size:1.1rem">$247,000</span></div>
  </div>
</div></section>

<section class="sd" id="blueprint"><div class="sd-inner reverse reveal">
  <div class="sd-text">
    <div class="section-label">Service 02</div>
    <h2>Growth System Blueprint</h2>
    <div class="sd-price">$3,000</div>
    <p>Most owners who get the audit know exactly what's broken — but then it sits in a folder because there's no time to build the system. The blueprint solves that. You get everything from the audit plus a complete, ready-to-implement growth system.</p>
    <p style="font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;">What you walk away with: a complete growth system your team can run — phone scripts, follow-up sequences, tracking dashboards, and a 90-day calendar telling you exactly what to do each week. No marketing manager required.</p>
    <ul class="sd-features">
      <li>Complete Revenue Leak Audit included</li>
      <li>Custom channel strategy with budget allocation — exactly where to put each dollar</li>
      <li>Phone scripts and CSR booking framework — word-for-word, ready to train from</li>
      <li>5-touch estimate follow-up sequence with templates your team uses tomorrow</li>
      <li>Review generation system with outreach templates</li>
      <li>Pre-built KPI dashboard so you can see what's working every week</li>
      <li>90-day implementation calendar with specific weekly actions</li>
      <li>5–8 ready-to-use template files included</li>
    </ul>
    <a href="mailto:hello@builtontenth.com?subject=Growth Blueprint" class="btn-primary">Apply for a Blueprint &rarr;</a>
  </div>
  <div class="sd-visual">
    <h3>What your blueprint includes</h3>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Channel strategy</span><span class="amber">Custom mix</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Budget allocation map</span><span class="amber">By channel</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Phone handling scripts</span><span class="amber">2-3 scripts</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>CSR qualification framework</span><span class="amber">Step-by-step</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Estimate follow-up sequence</span><span class="amber">5-touch</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Review generation system</span><span class="amber">Automated</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Weekly KPI dashboard</span><span class="amber">Pre-built</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Implementation calendar</span><span class="amber">90 days</span></div>
  </div>
</div></section>

<section class="sd" id="advisory"><div class="sd-inner reveal">
  <div class="sd-text">
    <div class="section-label">Service 03</div>
    <h2>90-Day Growth Advisory</h2>
    <div class="sd-price">$7,500</div>
    <p>The gap between knowing what's broken and actually fixing it is execution. Most owners implement 20% of what they find in an audit. The advisory exists so that doesn't happen to you.</p>
    <p style="font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;">What you walk away with: a business that actually runs on data — tracked, adjusted, and optimized every week for 90 days, with a before/after report proving what changed and a 6-month roadmap for what's next.</p>
    <ul class="sd-features">
      <li>Complete audit and blueprint delivered in week 1</li>
      <li>12 weeks of weekly written performance reviews — what's working, what's not, what to do</li>
      <li>Priority async access — questions answered in 24–48 hours, in writing</li>
      <li>Monthly competitor re-benchmarking so you know if the gap is closing</li>
      <li>Implementation troubleshooting — when something isn't working, we figure out why</li>
      <li>Exit report: before/after analysis showing exactly what changed in 90 days</li>
      <li>6-month forward roadmap so you know what to do after we're done</li>
    </ul>
    <a href="mailto:hello@builtontenth.com?subject=90-Day Advisory" class="btn-primary">Apply for Advisory &rarr;</a>
  </div>
  <div class="sd-visual">
    <h3>What 90 days looks like</h3>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Weeks 1-2</span><span class="amber">Audit + Blueprint delivery</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Weeks 3-4</span><span class="amber">Quick wins implementation</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Weeks 5-8</span><span class="amber">System build + optimization</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Weeks 9-12</span><span class="amber">Measurement + iteration</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Weekly deliverable</span><span style="color:#fff">Written performance review</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Monthly deliverable</span><span style="color:#fff">Full progress report</span></div>
    <div class="sd-row"><span>Exit deliverable</span><span style="color:#fff">Before/after + 6-month roadmap</span></div>
  </div>
</div></section>

<section class="faq-section"><div class="faq-inner">
  <h2>Common questions</h2>
  <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open');this.nextElementSibling.style.maxHeight=this.classList.contains('open')?'300px':'0'">Do I need to get on a phone call?</div><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">No. Everything is delivered in writing. You send us your company details, we do the research, and you receive a documented report you can reference, share with your team, and act on at your own pace. No calls, no video meetings, no presentations.</div></div></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open');this.nextElementSibling.style.maxHeight=this.classList.contains('open')?'300px':'0'">Will I actually be able to implement the findings?</div><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Yes — that's the whole point. Every finding comes with a specific action: what to do, who does it, and how long it takes. Most findings don't require technical skills or a marketing team. The most common ones — fixing GBP, starting a review request system, training a CSR script — can be done in a few hours by you or an office admin.</div></div></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open');this.nextElementSibling.style.maxHeight=this.classList.contains('open')?'300px':'0'">How is this different from a marketing agency?</div><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Agencies manage campaigns for monthly retainers and benefit financially when you spend more on ads. We don't run ads, don't take retainers, and have zero financial incentive to recommend more spend. Our only product is analysis — which means our only incentive is getting the analysis right.</div></div></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open');this.nextElementSibling.style.maxHeight=this.classList.contains('open')?'300px':'0'">What if I already have a marketing agency?</div><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Even better. The audit will show you whether your agency is performing or underperforming — with specific data points to hold them accountable. Most owners who get an audit discover their agency is tracking the wrong metrics and missing the numbers that actually connect to revenue.</div></div></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open');this.nextElementSibling.style.maxHeight=this.classList.contains('open')?'300px':'0'">What size company is this for?</div><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">HVAC, roofing, and plumbing companies doing $1M–$5M annually with 5–30 employees spending at least $3,000/month on marketing. If you're smaller, start with our free tools — they're built specifically for your stage.</div></div></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open');this.nextElementSibling.style.maxHeight=this.classList.contains('open')?'300px':'0'">What is the typical ROI?</div><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">The average audit identifies $100K–$400K in annual revenue leakage from a combination of missed calls, weak GBP presence, untracked ad spend, and zero follow-up on unbooked estimates. Fixing even one finding typically pays for the audit 20–50x over in the first year.</div></div></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open');this.nextElementSibling.style.maxHeight=this.classList.contains('open')?'300px':'0'">How long does the audit take and what do you need from me?</div><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">7 business days from when you send us your company details. We need: your company name, service area, website URL, and any active ad accounts or platforms you're using. That's it — we handle all the research from public data and our analysis tools.</div></div></div>
</div></section>

</Base>
